To set up Visual Studio Code on a Linux operating system, follow these steps:
1. Download VSC from https://code.visualstudio.com/download.
2. Install the C/C++ extension by typing "C/C++" in the search box and selecting the Microsoft extension.
3. Restart VSC by pressing the "Reload" button.
4. Add a tasks.json file to your project with the following content:
```json
{
    "version": "2.0.0",
    "tasks": [{
            "label": "Build with gcc",
            "type": "shell",
            "command": "gcc",
            "args": ["-g", "-std=c11", "-pedantic-errors",
                "-Wall", "-o", "program.exe", "${file}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Build with make",
            "type": "shell",
            "command": "make"
        }
    ]
}
```
5. Save the file and close it. Now, you can build your C or C++ programs

