To create a universal Makefile, you can use the following JSON format:
{
    "version": "2.0.0",
    "tasks": [
        {
            "label": "Build with gcc",
            "type": "shell",
            "command": "gcc",
            "args": ["-g", "-std=c11", "-pedantic-errors",
                "-Wall", "-o", "program.exe", "${file}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Build with make",
            "type": "shell",
            "command": "make"
        }
    ]
}
This Makefile will allow you to build the program using either gcc or make.

